 :tx/rationale "Create task: ACP-11: MCP tool responses as ActionProjection — braid_status, braid_task_ready, braid_next emit ACP (INV-BUDGET-007, INV-INTERFACE-010). BACKGROUND: MCP tools should emit the same ActionProjection as their CLI counterparts (INV-INTERFACE-010 semantic equivalence). Currently MCP tools call the same kernel functions but format output independently. With ACP, the MCP handler calls the projection builder and renders for the MCP context. The MCP tool response includes: content[0].text = projection.project(mcp_budget), where mcp_budget is derived from the MCP tool call's context (if provided) or defaults to Navigate strategy (~100 tokens). JSON output includes the full ActionProjection as structured data. APPROACH: Update mcp.rs handlers for braid_status, braid_task_ready, braid_next to use projection builders from ACP-5/6/10. MCP response text = projection rendered at Navigate level. JSON includes action, context_blocks, evidence_pointer as structured fields. Tests: (A) MCP braid_status response includes action. (B) MCP response <= 150 tokens (Navigate ceiling). (C) MCP JSON includes structured ActionProjection. FILE: crates/braid/src/mcp.rs"
